-- Sumitomo Mitsui Bank's Six-Month Profit May Climb to Record, Yomiuri Says
-- B y   S t u a r t   B i g g s
-- 2010-10-23T02:44:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-23/sumitomo-mitsui-bank-s-six-month-profit-may-climb-to-record-yomiuri-says.html
Sumitomo Mitsui Banking Corp. will
raise its interim profit forecast for the six months ended
September to a record 350 billion yen ($4.3 billion), the
Yomiuri newspaper reported today, without saying where it
obtained the information.  The change may raise six-month profit at parent company
Sumitomo Mitsui Financial Group Inc. to 400 billion yen, the
report said. The revision is expected to be announced early next
week, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stuart Biggs in Tokyo at 
